                    <span>You will not only feel your own presence but that of Eckhart's. This man's energy alone shifts you into your own being.<br>If you're sensitive you'll really know it. If you're not then this CD will help you to start to be.<br>I highly recommend this CD.<br>Eckhart is a wonderful teacher. I urge you to let him be your teacher to.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Not the best presentation of Eckhart's ideas</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>2</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>155</span>
                      /
                      <span>164</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2002-11-24</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I bought the "Power of Now" a few months ago and, of course, Amazon[.com] made note of it in their database. But that's a GOOD thing because they recently notified me about Eckhart Tolle's new offerings: "The Realization of Being" - and - "Even the Sun Will Die"
<br />
<br />I loved "The Power of Now" - a book, I feel, EVERYone would benefit from owning and reading time and time again. (A helpful practice until you 'get it' and can apply the concepts, his teachings to your daily life)
<br />
<br />And because I enjoyed this book so much, I went ahead and ordered both of the reccomended tapes (actually, CDs).
<br />
<br />"Even the Sun Will Die" is a beautiful work of art - and, like "The Power of Now" - is something you can (and WILL) listen to over and over and over again. DEFINITELY worth owning!
<br />
<br />But "The Realization of Being" was a BIG disappointment. No, wait - A HUGE disappointment! ! !
<br />
<br />It's obvious this particular CD is a recording of a workshop he gave somewhere, at some time - and that's all fine and good EXCEPT - it's like the workshop was a 4 hour event - and this tape only gives you hours # 2 and 3. So, you 'come in late' (and have to play catch-up) - and then the second CD bails out without a proper closing. Heck, you even hear Eckhart say on the tape: "We're going to take a lunch break now." - and then, that's it!
<br />
<br />So, after thoroughly enjoying "The Power of Now" and "Even the Sun Will Die" - you can imagine how let-down I felt after hearing this "haphazardly thrown together piece of mish-mosh".
<br /> 
<br />Eckhart's a fine man - one of the folks who'll definitely lead us into the new era of unconditional love and peace - but this particular tape (as far as I'm concerned) is an embarrasment - and truly NOT the way to present the views and guidance of such a talented soul.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Pure Power</div>
