                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">The magic of being.</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>41</span>
                      /
                      <span>42</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2002-05-24</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Eckhardt Tolle's "THE REALIZATION OF BEING" provides the listener with a genuine opportunity to experience the subject of this recorded seminar:  being, and all the aliveness that goes with it.  In the first CD, Tolle discusses what it's like to live in the moment and what drives us out of the moment.  By the second CD, Tolle's speaking pace drops significantly, so that listeners can experience the energy of their being during silence.  The tone of this audio CD is calm and meditative.  In fact, a disclaimer on the back cover cautions not to listen to the program while driving or operating heavy machinery due to the meditative nature of the recording.  In his generally quiet way, (with occasional bursts of faster and more energetic speaking) Tolle guides listeners to the richness of living from the state of being, not from thinking.  We're all very good at thinking, he says, but being requires practice.  Another great way to practice living in the moment is through the work of authors Ariel and Shya Kane - read their book "WORKING ON YOURSELF DOESN'T WORK" or listen to one of their audiotapes, such as "THE PRINCIPLES OF TRANSFORMATION."  On the subject of living life as magically as it is intended to be, Tolle and the Kanes represent a rare and great guiding force.</span>
                  
              
